# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ROS 2 colcon build artifacts
# These are regenerated by `colcon build` and should never be committed.
# They are also huge — often hundreds of megabytes.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
build/
install/
log/

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Python compiled files
# __pycache__ folders and .pyc files are regenerated automatically
# every time Python runs your scripts.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg-info/

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# C++ build artifacts (for when you start task 4.5)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
*.o
*.so
*.a
cmake-build-*/

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Editor and IDE files
# These encode personal preferences that shouldn't be forced on
# anyone else who clones your repo.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp       # vim swap files
*~          # backup files from various editors
.DS_Store   # macOS folder metadata (harmless but unnecessary)

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ROS 2 specific
# rosbag recordings can be gigabytes — keep them out of the repo
# unless you have a specific reason to commit a small reference bag.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
*.db3
*.mcap
rosbag2_*/

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Maps — this one is a judgment call
# The .pgm files can be large; many people commit them anyway
# because they are part of the project. For now, KEEP them tracked,
# so leave these two lines COMMENTED OUT.
# Uncomment if your maps balloon past a few megabytes.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# maps/*.pgm
# maps/*.yaml

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OS-level junk
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Secrets — never commit API keys, passwords, or WiFi credentials
# Your ESP32 firmware currently has WiFi credentials hardcoded.
# If you ever extract those into a separate config file, add it here.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
*.env
secrets.yaml
credentials.json
